screen_name: In my covid isolation boredom I have worked out that in the last 37 days I have had a fever at least once a day for 27 of them... Question is does that now make me hot?! 😂😂#Covid_19 #hot #COVID19
@LtotheJtotheP @jonathanshalit 😂😂 I've learnt the skills of sleeping for 16-18 hours of the day and coping with a fever for 12 days straight! Does that count?

Day 8 of covid and I think I've run out of new symptoms to try out! Fingers crossed the 3pm fever doesn't arrive today and I can feel like I'm making progress. Oh and if someone has found all my energy could you drop it back?! #covidtired #coronavirus #COVID19

Day 3 of suspected covid- started the day with fever and rigors and its not got much better! Husband confirmed positive covid so just waiting for my result to confirm the same. This is no fun at all. #StayHomeSaveLives #COVID19 #coronavirus
Day 17 in the Covid19 house... All is calm, all is quiet. Mostly because my right ear is so bloody sensitive to noise it has to be quiet or I think my head may explode #Covid_19 #Symptoms 😢

Finally got the result of my Covid-19 test... POSITIVE! What a surprise considering I've had every symptom there was but thankfully not had serious symptoms that required hospital treatment. I count myself very lucky for that ❤️

@LtotheJtotheP This is the truth. I think I've had a new symptom every single day. Day 8 and still getting mild fevers. And I'll feel better for a couple of hours and then BAM here's another symptom! Hope you are getting better xx
Husband now has fever, myalgia, headache, cough and chest tightness. As both frontline NHS workers it's not surprising but hate seeing him ill, and wish him a speedy recovery #coronavirus
